  "27": {
    "inputs": {
      "value": "Extreme macro close-up of a single soap bubble suspended in mid-air at the fragile instant just before it bursts, filling most of the frame. Its impossibly thin spherical surface swirls with shifting iridescent color — bands of magenta, electric blue, gold, and green flowing into one another like marbled oil on water, the thin-film interference patterns smeared into soft curving ribbons across the dome. Near the top, the film has thinned to near-transparency, a creeping dark patch where it is about to rupture, with the faintest beginning of a tear catching the light. Tiny pinpoint highlights and a soft window-shaped reflection sit on the bubble's curved surface, and a warped, miniature reflection of the surroundings bends across its belly. A few microscopic droplets cling to the underside. The bubble rests against a deep, smooth, near-black background so the colors glow. Soft, broad, diffused side-lighting from the left — a large softbox raking across the curve — sculpts the sphere and makes the iridescence luminous without harsh glare, with a subtle cool rim of light on the right edge. Shot on a 100mm macro lens, f/5.6 for a sharp band of focus across the surface swirls, ISO 100, studio strobe at high shutter speed to freeze the film mid-motion. The clean, saturated, fine-grain rendering of Fujifilm Provia 100F — true, vivid color and crisp micro-contrast. Jewel-like, delicate, mesmerizing, hyper-detailed fine-art macro photography."
    },
    "class_type": "PrimitiveStringMultiline",
